        "text": "CinCPac 172033 gives views on night attacks in carrier duels. Lack of DDs is an insurmountable obstacle to date. CinCPac also suggests the possibility of the use of B-25 (or similar) from CVs for attack and then return to a field ashore. CinCPac 182017 again urges that planes be placed on CANTON · ISLAl'ID for defense. In the South Pacific the day was devoted to administrative matters of building bases and providing for their logistic support.",
        "degraded": true
